    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A coarse-textured white marble that is nearly pure calcium carbonate; it was used to build the first 152 feet of the Washington Monument in Washington, DC. It is quarried in Texas, Maryland, not in the state of Texas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
